Directions to Site 214: At sign to Appalachian Trail continue straight(in the direction you came and not up Goshen Prong Trail to the AT) - cross Goshen Prong (come up the bank via the tree root. very near the corner of Goshen Prong and Fish Camp Prong) and take the footpath (which is right on the edge of Fish Camp Prong) about 3/4 ml. until you see Silers Creek which crones the trail - do not cross the stream but proceed to the right through a patch or Rhododendron until you see the moss-covered ties or the old railroad grade - go up the railroad grade to a falls about 700 m upstream - a red flag on the trees marks the spot.
